# Nuxt 4

You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, NuxtJS, Vue 3, VueUse, and Tailwind.

For UI and styling see vue-nuxt-ui. Follow project lint and reuse rules; prefer types, const objects, arrow functions, descriptive names.

## Nuxt-specific Guidelines
- Follow Nuxt 4 directory structure (e.g., pages/, components/, composables/ under `app/` in this project).
- File-based routing in the pages/ directory; server routes in the server/ directory.
- Leverage Nuxt plugins for global functionality.
- Use useFetch and useAsyncData for data fetching.
- Utilize Nuxt's auto-imports for components and composables.
- Implement SEO best practices using Nuxt's useHead and useSeoMeta.

## Key Conventions
- Use VueUse for common composables and utility functions; use Pinia for state management.

## Performance
- Leverage Nuxt's built-in performance optimizations; use Suspense for async components, lazy loading for routes and components. Optimize images: WebP, size data, lazy loading. Optimize Web Vitals (LCP, CLS, FID).

Follow the official Nuxt.js and Vue.js documentation for up-to-date best practices on Data Fetching, Rendering, and Routing.
